    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nTreesitter: deleting buffer changes syntax highlighting of another buffer.\n\nThis is bisected to 285c04e2d0e3adc2a05d6fd8d0fdcee313ec1b08.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Run `nvim --clean`\n2. Run `:edit $VIMRUNTIME/indent.vim`, which uses `vim` syntax highlighting\n3. Run `:vsplit $VIMRUNTIME/filetype.lua`, which uses treesitter highlighting\n4. Run `:bdelete`\n5. The syntax highlighting in `indent.vim` (shown by `:set syntax?`) has changed from `vim` to `lua`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe syntax highlighting in `indent.vim` shouldn't change\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-1038+g1e20f31aa3\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.42.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
