        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Echoing here, but my current (vibes-based, unverified; will be able to check in a bit) conclusion is that this isn't specifically a bug in that PR, but a consequence of `FileType` autocmds assuming `curbuf` is `<abuf>`. Maybe wrapping `TSHighlighter:destroy`'s `nvim_exec_autocmds(\"FileType\", ...)` call in `nvim_buf_call` might fix it?\n\n**Edit**: yeah it looks like wrapping in `nvim_buf_call` fixes it for me locally, so I guess that's what's going on. ðŸ« \n\nThe reason this bug didn't manifest before is because previously `on_detach` occurred too late, after the memfile was closed, so the `nvim_buf_is_loaded` check returns false, and this logic was skipped.   ",
